race.comment: DECORATION (1) dropped back in trip last start and was a touch disappointing in stronger company at Belmont. His run at this track and trip two back in the Coolgardie Cup was brilliant and that level stacks up highly in this event. Can take up the running and give his rivals something to chase. THE JESTER'S SON (6) settled last and unleashed a sharp sprint to pick up his rivals and put them to the sword, scoring by 2L and running very fast splits over this track and trip. The inside draw may see him a touch closer in the run and he drops plenty of weight as he rises in grade. Big chance on the back of that effort. MORE THAN ENUFF (3) boasts a strong record over this course and distance and turned in a strong effort over the mile at Belmont most recently. Back onto a Good track looks a positive too and he can play a leading role. FEUDING (2) finished behind THE JESTER'S SON last time out and now gets Pike. Key player. PLEASE MIZTER (5) is chasing the hat-trick and has winning claims.
